dismissalComment.html: its the best connection that Murtagh got on the ball. It flies towards the long-off boundary and Naib takes the catch. Afghanistan win by 39 runs.

headshotImage.longCaption: Mohammad Shahzad player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c sub (Gulbadin Naib) b Dawlat Zadran
dismissalText.commentary: Tim Murtagh c sub (Gulbadin Naib) b Dawlat Zadran 7 (11b 0x4 0x6) SR: 63.63

commentTextItems.html: its the best connection that Murtagh got on the ball. It flies towards the long-off boundary and Naib takes the catch. Afghanistan win by 39 runs.

commentPostTextItems.html: Afghanistan have produced a comprehensive win here today beating Ireland by 39 runs. Ed Joyce top scored for Ireland with 62 off 87 balls but once Kevin O'Brien was out for his quick fire 35 off 23, there was only going to be one winner.
Spinners was the pick of the Afghan bowlers, with Mohammad Nabi and Rashid taking 3 wickets each.
So Afghanistan go 1-0 up in the series. The great news is there is not long to wait till the next match. Thursday here at Stormont.
The weather for Thursday looks good, so thanks for following my commentary today and I hope that you join me again on Thursday.

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Shahzad c Dockrell b O'Brien 66 (79b 8x4 1x6) SR: 83.54

dismissalComment.html: Big Wicket there for Ireland. Shahzad hits the ball in the air to wide long-on. Dockrell gets under the ball and takes a simple catch. Shame that, Shahzad had just started hitting out.

dismissalText.commentary: Rahmat Shah lbw b Chase 14 (26b 0x4 0x6) SR: 53.84

dismissalComment.html: that's another wicket for Ireland. Rahmat looks to clip the ball into the legside, he didn't move his feet and gets hit in front of the stumps. The Umpire Ramage raises the finger.

dismissalText.commentary: Asghar Afghan c Dockrell b O'Brien 0 (7b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: oh no what has Stanikzai done? He comes down the wicket and hits the ball straight to Dockrell at mid-on. Afghanistan's captain has gone for a duck!

dismissalText.commentary: Samiullah Shinwari b Dockrell 24 (35b 2x4 0x6) SR: 68.57

dismissalComment.html: Dockrell gets one to spin in on Shenwari and can't believe that he has been bowled

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Nabi lbw b O'Brien 5 (10b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: O'Brien gets his fourth wicket. Nabi wants to clip the ball through the legside, he misses and gets hit on the pad. It looked out from here and we are square of the wicket!

headshotImage.caption: Barry McCarthy player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Barry McCarthy player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Najibullah Zadran c Stirling b McCarthy 59 (61b 6x4 2x6) SR: 96.72

dismissalComment.html: that the big wicket for Ireland. Its another short ball from McCarthy, Najibullah mis-times the ball and it flies high in the air. Stirling gets under the ball at extra cover and takes the catch

headshotImage.caption: Barry McCarthy player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Barry McCarthy player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mirwais Ashraf c McBrine b McCarthy 12 (12b 2x4 0x6) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: that looks a lovely shot from Ashraf, he helps the ball towards the long leg boundary. It holds up in the wind and McBrine takes the catch. The batsmen crossed so Rashid is on strike.

dismissalText.commentary: Dawlat Zadran c Poynter b McCarthy 7 (9b 1x4 0x6) SR: 77.77

dismissalComment.html: what a catch from Poynter. Its another short ball down the legside and Dawlat looks to pull the ball. He gets a tiny edge on the ball and Poynter dives to his left to take the catch. Dawlat can't believe he is out and just stands there.
